{"word":"συννοέω","slug":"συννοέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>συννοέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to meditate</i> or <i>reflect upon</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to perceive by thinking, comprehend, understand</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:— so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}